title: Tuesday Training Criterium
registration:
Register at the event.  $2.

Additional $5 one day license if you don\'t have a USA Cycling license
notes:
These are very laid back practice races.  No numbers, no prizes, just go out, practice cornering in a group, and get some good sprint workouts in.

Series of short track-style events.  A, B, Junior, Women categories.  May be combined depending on attendance.

Events may include Scratch race, points race, miss & out, etc.  If you don\'t know what all of this means, we\'ll explain it when you get there.

Categories rotate.  Everyone will get started at 6:30 or shortly after.  Everyone will have at least 2-3 events per night in which they can participate.
directions: Just south of the Jesse Owens Track Center on Fred Taylor Drive between Ackerman and Lane.

title: Ride On Wooster Crit at the Roses
Madeira Centennial Criterium
description: The Madeira Centennial Race Committee is pleased to announce continuation of the first-ever bike race held in the heart of Madeira:  The 3rd Annual Madeira Centennial Criterium, Friday,  June 29th 2012. All categories of criterium racers will be competing from 4:30pm – 9:30pm.  Complete with music, food, beer tent, and kids events.  Cyclists will battle for over $5500 in cash and merchandise.  Fun for all!
course: One mile circuit through downtown Madeira (10 miles north of downtown Cincinnati).  5-turn technical course with a short climb/descent, and 2 right-hand 180s.
registration: Pre-registration is available on BikeReg.com through June 27 at 10:00pm.  Day-of registration is available on-site for an additional $10.  Link to pre-reg: https://www.bikereg.com/Net/15827
directions:
DIRECTIONS:  From Columbus I-71 South, take the Montgomery Rd exit 12.  Turn left on Montgomery Rd.  Turn right on Hosbrook.  At dead end, turn left on Euclid.  Parking will be off of Euclid as you reach Madeira, look for parking signage.

From downtown Cincinnati to I-71 North, take the Kenwood Rd exit 11.  Right turn on Kenwood.  First left turn on Euclid.  Parking will be off of Euclid as you reach Madeira, look for parking signage.

title: Hyde Park Blast Criterium - USA Crits Series #8
description: One day road criterium in downtown Hyde Park, part of full day of festivities including 4-mile run, bike race, and block party featuring Cowboy Mouth!
course: One mile circuit running along Erie Ave, with a 180 turn around Hyde Park Square at west end of course, and a slightly technical 4 corners on the east end of course.
registration: Pre-registration available on BikeReg.com beginning March 15th - June 28th.  Raceday registration available on-site for an additional $10 for categories that are not closed out.
notes: Reserved team parking spaces will be emailed out upon the conclusion of pre-registration.  Teams with 3 or more riders registered will receive one team parking space per 3 riders registered.
directions:
From Columbus and areas north of Cincinnati: take I-71 South to Dana/Montgomery exit.  Turn left onto Dana.  Continue straight onto Dana Ave as it becomes Observatory Ave.  Turn left onto Paxton Ave.  Reserved team parking, turn left onto Erie Ave.  All other parking turn right onto Erie Ave and park along street.

Areas south of Cincinnati: Take I-75 North to downtown Cincinnatio,  take I-71 North at the split once you cross the Ohio River.  Take Dana Ave exit.  Turn left at Duck Creek.  Turn right onto Dana Ave.  Continue straight onto Dana Ave as it becomes Observatory Ave.  Turn left onto Paxton Ave.  Reserved team parking, turn left onto Erie Ave.  All other parking turn right onto Erie Ave and park along street.

title: Jeremy Powers Cincinnati Cyclocross clinic present
North Coast Gran Prix of Cyclocross
Harbin Park Short Track MTB Race
Ohio State Cyclocross Championship Master & Junior
Ohio State Cyclocross Championship Category Event
Cincy3: Lionheart International at Kings CX
Cincy3 Harbin Park
description: The final day of the Cincy3 weekend of cyclocross racing!  The Harbin Park cyclocross event has been held continuously since 1996 - making it one of the longest running events in the Midwest.
course: Gradually hilly course with a mix of high speed and low speed turns, open hammer sections, big runup, and two trips through the sandpit.
registration: Pre-register via BikeReg.com through the link supplied.  Pre-registration closes on Wednesday, October 31 at 10:00pm.  Registration is available onsite for an additional $10 fee.
notes: Amateur races are part of the OVCX Series (www.ovcx.com).  Elite races are sanctioned through the UCI.
directions:
Directions to Harbin Park: (Google: 1300 Hunter Rd.  Fairfield, Ohio  45014)
From Michigan and areas north of Cincinnati : from I-71 and I-75 South, as you are approaching Cincinnati, take I-275 West to exit 36 (Mt. Healthy). Turn right at exit ramp onto 127 and head 2 miles north. Turn left on Hunter Rd. Continue for 1 mile on Hunter Rd. and it runs into Harbin Park. Parking is up the hill on the right/backup parking is on your way in on the left. Bathrooms are behind ranger station near playground.
